Michelangelo (The Colour Library of Art)
Paul Hamlyn | 1968 | ISBN: 0600037843 | English | 96 pages | PDF | 13.7 MB

Just as his mighty St Peter's dome dominates the city of Rome, so Michelangelo dominates Renaissance Italy. In his own lifetime and ever since he was universally acclaimed as one of the greatest creative figures in the history of art. For him art was a compelling inner calling. He saw painting, sculpture and architecture as one art involving the same problems: an extraordinary cohesion and harmony characterizes his work
